      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While short-term high doses are sometimes used to correct severe deficiencies, a blanket \"front-loading\" strategy without knowing your baseline is risky. Your body processes vitamins differently, and a rapid spike can be stressful on your system. I strongly recommend at least a minimal blood test to get a true picture, or at least ask your pharmacist for advice on a safe, moderate loading dose.",
      "source": "target",
